ies, incurred Wimbledon's wrath by consorting with ball boys, wrote fiction under the pen name of Ned Litam. He now plays with those balls on Elysian turf. Shall we spare his shade?





Cordial greetings

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: PROF. ALFRED APPEL, JR.

CC, 1 p.





Montreux, April 3, 1967

